SOCCER 10 POOL OF THE DAYThursday 26 May S10 V2 Former winners Corinthians and Boca Juniors are at home tonight in their final set of group phase matches in South America’s Copa Libertadores and expected to advance to the last-16. More details at www.soccer6.co.za. M1 Kayserispor vs Sivasspor: The Turkish Cup final ends the season. Kayserispor won in 2008 but this is Sivasspor’s first appearance in the final.M2 Sarpsborg vs Molde: Sarpsborg are unbeaten in their last six home games against Molde who have won their last four outings, conceding just once.M3 Pyramids vs Future: Pyramids are second in the Egyptian league, five points ahead of fourth paced Future.M4 Breidablik UBK vs Valur Reykjavik: Breidablik have won all seven games of the new Iceland season and are already five points ahead of their nearest rivals. Valur have 13 points from their seven games in fourth place.M5 Athletico Paranaense vs Caracas: Brazil’s Athletico share top place in Group B of the Copa Libertadores but have just one point more than Caracas of Venezuela, who would need away success to advance to the last-16.M6 Libertad vs The Strongest: Libertad are tie at the top of Copa Libertadores Group B with Athletico Paranaense on seven points, while The Strongest have six points.M7 FBC Melgar vs Cuiaba: Brazil’s Cuiaba would need an away win to advance in the Copa Sudamericana but their Peruvian hosts need only one point.M8 Boca Juniors vs Deportivo Cali: Boca were Copa Libertadores runners-up four years ago and are third in Group E, but just one point behind co-leaders Cali and Corinthians and with a win should be able to progress.M9 Corinthians vs Always Ready: Corinthians have a chance to win their Copa Libertadores group but their Bolivian visitors have already been eliminated from the race.M10 Junior vs Union de Sante Fe: Junior top their Copa Sudamericana group and a draw would be good enough to ensure progress. Union are second but if they lose, or even draw, could find themselves eliminated. Suggested permutation: R4.00 1 x 3 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 1,2